  "prompt": "What does President Duterte think of Donald Trump?",
  "response": "President Rodrigo Duterte of the Philippines has expressed mixed feelings about former President Donald Trump throughout his time in office. Initially, Duterte was supportive of Trump, appreciating his straightforwardness and tough stance on certain issues, such as the fight against drugs and terrorism. Duterte's admiration was partly due to Trump's perceived desire to strengthen U.S.-Philippines relations.\n\nHowever, Duterte has also criticized the United States as a whole and, at times, Trump specifically, especially regarding human rights concerns related to Duterte's controversial anti-drug campaign. He often highlighted his intention to pursue an independent foreign policy, balancing relations with both the U.S. and China.\n\nOverall, while Duterte has shown a level of admiration for Trump's leadership style, he has also been critical of U.S. pressure on human rights issues. Their relationship can be characterized as pragmatic with elements of respect, but it is also influenced by broader geopolitical dynamics and Duterte's own agenda.",
